#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:1
msgid "Add the vtkCriticalTime filter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:3
msgid ""
"Given an input that changes over time, the `vtkCriticalTime` filter "
"generates a new data array containing time step values. These values "
"correspond to the time at which a specified threshold criterion has been met "
"for a given point/cell array (at each point/cell respectively)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:7
msgid ""
"To do so, the filter needs to process all available timesteps. The output of "
"the filter in not temporal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:9
msgid ""
"Like in the `vtkThreshold` filter, the threshold criterion can take three "
"forms:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:10
msgid "greater than a particular value;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:11
msgid "less than a particular value;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-critical-time-threshold-filter.md:12
msgid "between two values."
msgstr ""
